Title: 99 Red Balloons
Comment:
This is a fun party song from the 80s, right? 

No — its about a nuclear holocaust. 

The song, released during the Cold War by the West German band Nena, tells the story of a civilian letting go of "red balloons," mistakenly registered by an early warning system as enemy missiles, eventually leading to nuclear war.

"Panic bells, it's red alert...
The war machine springs to life...
It's all over and I'm standing pretty,
In this dust that was a city"

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fpu5a0Bl8eY
